LG Electronics has introduced OLED TV with cutting edge technology which will give customers an easy-on-the eyes experience. According to the company, the OLED TV has low blue light emission, flicker elimination, and offers no discomfort
glare or fear of eyesight deterioration concerns for viewers. The general manager, LG Electronics West Africa operations, home entertainment, TV Division, Mr Choong Bae
Seok says, “Nowadays, consumers want a TV that shows the world naturally, just as it is. At LG, we’ve been working hard to make OLED technology deliver such a natural realism. To do so, we’re improving three major aspects: picture quality, eye comfort, and environmental friendliness.’’ Seok said from the customer journey standpoint, “the television is evolving into a communication device
that connects people and machines. Gaming TVs.” Seok said the new television has feature functions that are geared for new consoles such
as the PS5 and X-Box series. For home training, there are TVs that rotate into Portrait Mode. In addition, portable TVs are becoming increasingly popular. However, we believe this is insufficient. We anticipate that consumers can now choose OLED TVs with more confidence,’’ Seok added. LG Electronics also said in a statement that people are beginning to pay more attention to protecting their eyes
and that long screen exposure can yield undesirable side effects.